snippet: Output at manufacturing plants rose 0.2 percent in October because of rising demand for machinery, plastics, clothing and furniture.
abstract: Federal Reserve reports output at manufacturing plants rose 0.2 percent in October because of rising demand for machinery, plastics, clothing and furniture; automobile production fell 1.2 percent.
lead_paragraph: Output at manufacturing plants rose 0.2 percent in October because of rising demand for machinery, plastics, clothing and furniture.

headline.main: Factory Output Grows Modestly, as Auto Production Slows
headline.print_headline: Factory Output Grows Modestly, as Auto Production Slows
